What happens at a = 1 and r = 1? The *harmonic series* is the infinite
sum of the reciprocal of all the natural numbers:

1 + 1/2 + 1/3 + 1/4 + 1/5 + 1/6 + 1/7 + 1/8 +…. + 1/*n* + ….

The proof of that the harmonic series diverges is to compare the series
in blocks of powers of 2 to the clearly divergent series 1 + ½ + ½ + ½ +
….:

